Note: the `Month` index starts with `0` instead of `1`. Spent too much time on the bug.
**Method 1: Use Calendar rules**
1. convert `date` to `time = [year, month, day]`;
2. accumulate days except current month, `time[1]`; 
3. add the days in current month, `time[1]`;
4. if current month, `time[1]`, passed February and current year, `time[0]`, is leap year, add 1 to final result.
```
    private static final int[] month = {31, 28, 31, 30, 31, 30, 31, 31, 30, 31, 30, 31};
    public int dayOfYear(String date) {
        int[] time = Arrays.stream(date.split("-")).mapToInt(t -> Integer.parseInt(t)).toArray();
        int days = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < time[1] - 1; ++i) 
            days += month[i];
        return days + time[2] + (time[1] > 2 && (time[0] % 4 == 0 && time[0] % 100 != 0 || time[0] % 400 == 0) ? 1 : 0);
    }
```
----

**Method 2: Use API**
