solutions.content:
### Theory
You need to know how to calculate if a given year is a leap year. You will also need to know how many days there are in each month. If you don't know this information you really cannot progress with this question. Luckily its almost never asked in an interview setting for this exact reason.

### Solution
```
    private int[] daysPerMonth = new int[] {31, 28, 31, 30, 31, 30, 31, 31, 30, 31, 30, 31};

    public int dayOfYear(String date) {
        String[] parts = date.split("-");
        int year = Integer.parseInt(parts[0]), month = Integer.parseInt(parts[1]), day = Integer.parseInt(parts[2]);
        int dayCount = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < month - 1; i++) dayCount += daysPerMonth[i];
        dayCount += day;
        return isLeapYear(year) && month > 2 ? dayCount + 1 : dayCount;
    }

    private boolean isLeapYear(int year) {
        if (year % 4 != 0) return false;
        if (year % 100 == 0 && year % 400 != 0) return false;
        return true;
    }
```

