# Approach
I have provided 2 solutions, first one I believe is more correct due to less code and usage of relevant Calendar library, this one is slow but closest to real programming. 
Second solution is pointed on speeding up runtime by minimuzing usage of dependencies and some portion of hard coding. 

# Code
Slow but more correct solution with calendar. 
```
class Solution {
    func dayOfYear(_ date: String) -> Int {
        let components = date.components(separatedBy: "-")
        var dayNumber = Int(components[2])!
        let months = Int(components[1])!
        if months >= 2 {
            for month in 1..<months {
                let dateComponents = DateComponents(year: Int(components[0]), month: month)
                let calendar = Calendar.current
                dayNumber += calendar.range(of: .day, in: .month, for: calendar.date(from: dateComponents)!)!.count
            }
        }
        return dayNumber
    }
}
