# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
You will get two cases for year - leap year or not leap year. It is easy to find the day number for non-leap year but for leap year, again two cases - first, the date is in or before february, second, date is after february.
Create a array containing the list of days would be in each month for a non-leap year and run a loop for the month in which the date is occuring. It is easily understandable by seeing the code. 
Check for leap year if month is more than 2, if it is leap year then add 1 otherwise return the total.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: $$O(n)$$
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: $$O(1)$$
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

![image.png](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/62a373b7-293d-4886-b2ed-aa121ed9f439_1695042191.4267366.png)


# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int dayOfYear(String date) {
        int year = Integer.parseInt(date.substring(0, 4));
        int month = Integer.parseInt(date.substring(5, 7));
        int day = Integer.parseInt(date.substring(8));

        int[] days = {31, 28, 31, 30, 31, 30, 31, 31, 30, 31, 30, 31};

        int total = day;
        // add the days of the month which has passed for the year
        for(int i = 1; i < month; i++){
            total += days[i-1];
        }

        // check for leap year  
        if(year%4 == 0 && month > 2){
            // check for leap year for the year ending with '00
            if(year%100 == 0 && year%400 != 0){
                return total;
            }
            total++;
        }

        return total;
    }
}
```

